  "text": "Clonal integration significantly increased TOC, DOC and DON concentrations in the rhizosphere of shaded offspring ramets as well as C/N, whereas no effects of clonal integration on soil moisture, pH and TN were observed in the rhizosphere of shaded offspring ramets (Table 2 ). C mic and N mic were significantly higher in the rhizosphere of shaded, connected offspring ramets compared to shaded, severed offspring ramets (Table 2) . Concentrations of inorganic nitrogen (NH 4 + -N and NO [CITATION_1] 2 -N) in the rhizosphere of shaded offspring ramets were also markedly increased by clonal integration. Meanwhile, NH [CITATION_2] + -N concentration was evidently higher than NO [CITATION_3] 2 -N concentration, regardless of stolon connection or severing (Table 2) .",
